NARRATOR: In 1972, a crack commando unit
was sent to prison by a miIitary court...

00:59.313 --> 01:00.891
for a crime they didn't commit.

01:00.982 --> 01:03.899
These men promptIy escaped
from a maximum security stockade...

01:03.985 --> 01:05.443
to the Los AngeIes underground.

01:05.528 --> 01:09.146
Today, stiII wanted by the government,
they survive as soIdiers of fortune.

01:09.240 --> 01:11.731
If you have a probIem,
if no one eIse can heIp...

01:11.826 --> 01:15.242
and if you can find them,
maybe you can hire the A-Team.

01:17.957 --> 01:19.617
[Theme music]

02:32.698 --> 02:35.569
[Slow instrumental music]

02:55.137 --> 02:58.008
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

03:33.092 --> 03:36.543
That crazy old buzzard
just won't give it up, will he?

03:39.348 --> 03:42.848
We've got Griffin, and he's loaded
with supplies on his way to the mine.

03:42.935 --> 03:45.687
FLETCHER: ls he alone?
SCHECKTER: He sure is, Mr. FIetcher.

03:46.397 --> 03:48.888
See to it that he doesn't make it.

03:54.864 --> 03:57.153
[Suspenseful instrumental music intensifies]

04:00.494 --> 04:02.321
[Car brakes screeching]

04:33.945 --> 04:35.273
[Gun firing]

04:38.616 --> 04:41.487
Another winner! Good shooting, mister.

04:41.577 --> 04:45.195
Give the little lady anything she likes
on the side shelf.

04:45.540 --> 04:47.164
HANNlBAL: There you go, lady.

04:47.250 --> 04:49.657
HANNlBAL: Step right up and test your skill.

04:49.752 --> 04:52.955
Three shots for $1. Everybody's a winner.

04:56.801 --> 04:58.840
Three ducks,
pick anything on the side shelf.

04:58.928 --> 05:01.763
That's it, lady, step right up.
Another winner!

05:02.723 --> 05:05.724
Three ducks and take home
a teddy for Freddie.

05:07.144 --> 05:10.893
Lovely sweater, my dear.
Shoot a little low and to the left.

05:12.817 --> 05:14.441
[Gun firing]

05:15.820 --> 05:19.023
l'm on a cold streak, here. Another winner!

05:19.115 --> 05:21.985
Anything you like on the side shelf.

05:22.076 --> 05:24.781
l was told l might find
a gentleman here named Louie.

05:24.871 --> 05:27.362
Doesn't sound familiar.
What's his last name?

05:27.456 --> 05:29.366
l was supposed to meet him here at 10:00.

05:29.458 --> 05:30.869
HANNlBAL: What's your business?

05:30.960 --> 05:33.914
Carnival's a small place.
Maybe l can ask around.

05:34.088 --> 05:37.208
lt's not that sort of business.
Sorry l bothered you.

05:37.758 --> 05:39.668
Just a minute, lady.

05:39.760 --> 05:41.967
Everybody's a winner.

05:42.763 --> 05:45.052
Step right up and test your skill.

05:45.141 --> 05:46.635
Three shots for $1.

05:48.811 --> 05:50.768
l'm not sure l understand this.

05:50.897 --> 05:52.854
[Carnival music playing]

06:03.201 --> 06:04.363
TOBY: Hello.

06:06.746 --> 06:09.497
HANNlBAL: Come in, my dear.
You're looking for Louie?

06:09.582 --> 06:11.954
TOBY: Look, mister,
l don't know who you are...

06:12.251 --> 06:15.086
but for two weeks,
l've been waiting in empty warehouses...

06:15.171 --> 06:19.334
cheap hotels, and taking taxicabs
to meet someone in the middle of nowhere.

06:19.592 --> 06:22.379
TOBY: Are we just going to stare
at each other?

06:24.222 --> 06:27.425
HANNlBAL: lf you're looking for the A-Team,
Miss Griffin...

06:28.142 --> 06:29.850
you've found them.

06:29.936 --> 06:31.311
B.A...

06:33.731 --> 06:34.976
Face...

06:36.359 --> 06:37.557
Amy...

06:39.195 --> 06:40.523
Murdock.

06:44.742 --> 06:47.909
MURDOCK: Bogey the Bear Show.

06:48.579 --> 06:51.746
[Murdock singing silly song]

06:52.416 --> 06:53.959
B.A.: Get out of there, man.

06:56.087 --> 06:59.622
Now, Miss Griffin, why don't you tell us
what this is all about?

06:59.882 --> 07:01.211
AMY: Maybe l can help you out.

07:01.300 --> 07:03.376
AMY: You're the daughter
of an Australian national.

07:03.469 --> 07:06.387
Your father was a dreamer,
with a very colorful past.

07:06.472 --> 07:08.797
He was a lifer with the Bushnell Cavaliers.

07:08.891 --> 07:11.014
AMY: When he retired,
he went to South Africa...

07:11.102 --> 07:14.019
where he spent all of his time
prospecting diamond mines.

07:14.188 --> 07:15.730
Everybody thought he was nuts.

07:15.815 --> 07:17.891
Nuts! Now we're cooking!

07:18.484 --> 07:21.271
AMY: But you think he found one.
You think he was murdered.

07:21.362 --> 07:22.737
Right after he staked a claim.

07:22.822 --> 07:23.901
How do you know all that?

07:24.031 --> 07:27.198
Let's just say if we didn't,
you wouldn't have gotten this far.

07:27.994 --> 07:31.410
He had a dream.
All his life, he wanted his own mine.

07:32.164 --> 07:35.165
lt wasn't even the money.
lt was the romance of it.

07:35.251 --> 07:38.168
My father was like a big kid
when it came to that place.

07:38.254 --> 07:39.582
Who'd want to kill a big kid?

07:39.672 --> 07:40.870
TOBY: Jonathan Fletcher.

07:40.965 --> 07:43.088
He owns a piece
of every mine in South Africa.

07:43.176 --> 07:46.959
He wasn't about to let my father
have one little mine he could call his own.

07:47.054 --> 07:50.803
Now Fletcher can claim that mine
after 30 days, unless l can get it working.

07:50.892 --> 07:52.090
We don't work mines.

07:52.185 --> 07:53.809
l don't see how we can help you.

07:53.895 --> 07:57.939
With transport. Fletcher controls the
only road that leads to my father's mine...

07:58.149 --> 08:01.600
and l can't get any dynamite in
because he won't allow anyone through.

08:01.694 --> 08:05.145
Unless you can help me, l'm gonna
lose everything my father worked for.

08:05.239 --> 08:06.568
What do you want with dynamite?

08:06.657 --> 08:08.983
Wouldn't that
blow the diamonds everywhere?

08:09.076 --> 08:12.113
lt's not for the diamonds.
We have other equipment for that.

08:12.205 --> 08:15.953
lt's to blow out an airshaft
so we can work the lower levels of the mine.

08:16.042 --> 08:19.624
TOBY: But like l said,
l need somebody to get it up that road.

08:19.879 --> 08:24.126
That's what my father was trying to do
when Fletcher had him killed.

08:24.967 --> 08:28.217
l couldn't save his life,
but l can save his dream.

08:28.679 --> 08:30.339
l need your help.

08:30.681 --> 08:32.639
Give the lady an estimate, Face.

08:32.725 --> 08:36.094
With the cost overrides, perks,
per diems, light armaments...

08:36.187 --> 08:40.184
mileage bonus, $210,000.

08:41.107 --> 08:42.567
You've got to be kidding!

08:42.652 --> 08:45.606
South Africa's out of the zone.
We had to add 20%%.

08:45.696 --> 08:48.816
lf you pay peanuts, lady,
you wind up hiring monkeys.

08:55.790 --> 08:59.373
TOBY: lt's all l have. My father sent it to me
before he was murdered.

08:59.460 --> 09:02.710
Keep it as collateral,
and if you pull this off...

09:03.089 --> 09:06.540
l'll give you 10%% of the mine's find
in the first year.

09:11.055 --> 09:15.267
-What do you say, Face?
-Has a center flaw, but it will cut up nicely.

09:16.310 --> 09:17.852
Give it back.

09:22.692 --> 09:25.361
Miss Griffin, you just hired the A-Team.

09:25.444 --> 09:27.603
Pay us when we finish the job.

09:27.738 --> 09:30.989
Meet me at this address
the day after tomorrow.

09:33.703 --> 09:36.538
Bulawayo, Zulabwe....

09:39.333 --> 09:42.287
Bulawayo, Zulabwe?
Man, l ain't flying there!

09:42.461 --> 09:44.584
Of course you're not, B.A.

09:49.302 --> 09:51.840
[Upbeat instrumental music]

09:59.937 --> 10:03.935
Nurse, l want BP readings every six minutes.
Continue monitoring adrenalin levels.

10:04.025 --> 10:06.267
Slow down here a minute. What's going on?

10:06.360 --> 10:07.903
HANNlBAL: You must be Mr. Bellar.

10:07.987 --> 10:09.102
l don't know a Mr. Bellar.

10:09.197 --> 10:10.359
What are you doing?

10:10.448 --> 10:12.820
What's going on?
Bellar's supposed to expedite this.

10:12.909 --> 10:16.408
l can't let you board, l'm sorry.
l need to see some kind of paperwork.

10:16.495 --> 10:18.038
HANNlBAL: Paperwork, sir.

10:18.289 --> 10:22.785
Chief Babaracas must be on an operating
table in Johannesburg in 1 2 hours...

10:23.336 --> 10:24.794
or he will die.

10:25.338 --> 10:28.255
-Die?
-Yes, and on your airplane. Sign here.

10:30.593 --> 10:34.638
Sir, in a small way,
you have served medical science.

10:34.722 --> 10:39.183
The AMA thanks you,
the Chief thanks you, his tribe thanks you.

11:18.057 --> 11:19.432
[Hippo snorting]

11:19.517 --> 11:21.924
HANNlBAL: Come on, Murdock,
you're scaring the animals.

11:22.019 --> 11:24.012
FACE: You're also waking up B.A.

11:24.772 --> 11:27.856
B.A.: l said l wasn't flying to Africa,
but l'm here.

11:27.942 --> 11:31.275
l said l wasn't flying to no Borneo,
and l was there.

11:31.362 --> 11:33.687
The same with Mexico, Latin America...

11:33.781 --> 11:36.070
and anywhere else
you guys want to hustle me into.

11:36.158 --> 11:38.151
B.A., life's roads have many twists.

11:38.244 --> 11:41.245
l'm getting tired of all these tricks
you keep playing on me.

11:41.330 --> 11:42.528
This is the last time!

11:50.506 --> 11:52.166
There's the place.

11:58.139 --> 11:59.419
HANNlBAL: B.A.

12:00.016 --> 12:04.310
You hang around out here. You see any
governmental types, let us know.

12:08.774 --> 12:12.724
Take care of Bogey for me, will you?
He ain't old enough to drink yet.

12:12.820 --> 12:14.612
B.A.: The man's nuts!

12:14.989 --> 12:17.562
Bartender, give us a round of beers.

12:18.743 --> 12:21.613
There's nothing like a clandestine meeting.

12:21.704 --> 12:25.038
We could meet anywhere in Zulabwe
and Fletcher would know about it.

12:25.124 --> 12:26.915
TOBY: He owns the whole country.

12:27.168 --> 12:30.537
Anyway, l'm hiring people
who can handle themselves, right?

12:30.630 --> 12:34.627
But you're not paying us to be stupid.
Now, did you get the truck and supplies?

12:34.717 --> 12:36.176
Everything but the dynamite.

12:36.260 --> 12:38.834
The owner of the supply store
wouldn't sell it to me.

12:39.013 --> 12:40.211
Really?

12:41.849 --> 12:45.349
l'm a little light on wardrobe,
but maybe l can work something out.

12:45.436 --> 12:46.930
Shall we see what we can do?

12:47.021 --> 12:49.726
-You got it, Face-guy.
-Pleasure.

12:53.194 --> 12:56.479
Mr. Fletcher, this is Jake
down at the Come Lucky.

12:57.323 --> 13:00.407
Old man Griffin's kid
is talking some business.

13:06.832 --> 13:08.825
l don't know if this is gonna work.

13:08.918 --> 13:10.994
What country did you say
this uniform's from?

13:11.087 --> 13:13.412
Sherman Oaks Neighborhood Watch
and Parent Patrol.

13:13.506 --> 13:15.831
MURDOCK: What rank?
FACE: Chief Crossing Guard.

13:15.925 --> 13:19.376
-Terrific.
-Murdock, it's the singer, not the song.

13:27.353 --> 13:28.847
This'll work.

13:32.066 --> 13:36.111
-You think you can do it?
-Surely you must be jesting, old chap.

13:36.737 --> 13:38.611
After l saw Bridge on the River Kwai...

13:38.698 --> 13:41.533
it took me six months to realise
l wasn't Peter O'Toole.

13:42.201 --> 13:45.072
You mean Alec Guinness.
Peter O'Toole wasn't in that picture.

13:45.162 --> 13:48.033
He was, if you saw him through these eyes.

13:56.132 --> 13:57.211
[Moran coughing]

13:57.300 --> 14:00.254
Good afternoon, gents.
What can l do for you this afternoon?

14:00.344 --> 14:03.014
-Morey Moran?
-Yes.

14:03.181 --> 14:07.130
Then l can assume that these are
your initials on this purchase order.

14:07.226 --> 14:08.637
-M.M.?
-Yes.

14:09.812 --> 14:11.057
What are you doing?

14:11.147 --> 14:14.231
Calling Headquarters to tell them
we're questioning the suspect.

14:14.317 --> 14:15.431
Suspect? Wait a minute--

14:15.526 --> 14:19.606
You have already conceded, sir,
that your initials are on the document.

14:19.697 --> 14:23.446
Please do not complicate matters
by perjuring yourself.

14:23.534 --> 14:26.369
Look, l don't have to stand here
and take this from a....

14:26.454 --> 14:28.530
Who are you guys, anyway?

14:28.623 --> 14:32.371
That's Colonel Bradley Lexington,
Salisbury Explosives and Arms Control.

14:32.460 --> 14:35.165
l'm Edmund Morris,
United Nations attachÃ© to Zulabwe.

14:35.254 --> 14:36.832
l ain't done nothing wrong.

14:36.923 --> 14:40.457
Why don't you go put
somebody else's knickers in a twist?

14:41.552 --> 14:43.212
MURDOCK: We are not amused.

14:44.096 --> 14:47.762
MURDOCK: On 16 December, 1982,
this establishment sold...

14:47.850 --> 14:50.472
10 cases of dynamite
to the Parker Construction Company.

14:50.561 --> 14:51.759
Do you concur?

14:51.854 --> 14:55.021
So what? l'm a supply store. But--

14:55.107 --> 14:59.105
To continue, said dynamite was defective...

14:59.195 --> 15:01.234
and a premature explosion...

15:01.322 --> 15:05.189
caused the untidy demise
of 22 workers employed...

15:05.284 --> 15:09.152
to renovate the bridge at Breaker Pass.
How do you respond to that?

15:09.247 --> 15:10.955
By saying that's bloody impossible...

15:11.040 --> 15:13.827
'cause there ain't no bridge
over Breaker Pass, that's why.

15:13.918 --> 15:17.785
ldiot! There is no need
to brutalize the Queen's English...

15:17.880 --> 15:20.087
along with your other crimes,
which now include...

15:20.174 --> 15:23.128
impugning a loyal subject
of Her Royal Majesty!

15:23.344 --> 15:26.013
Come on, you guys must be kidding.

15:26.097 --> 15:28.802
l sell good stuff here,
and everyone knows it.

15:28.891 --> 15:30.718
Don't make me laugh.

15:31.477 --> 15:36.186
No kippers, no English herringbone tweeds,
no meat pies...

15:36.274 --> 15:38.432
no Rolls-Royce petrol caps...

15:38.526 --> 15:41.562
no original pressings of Hey Jude.

15:41.654 --> 15:44.227
You, sir, are a miserable excuse
for a shop keep.

15:44.323 --> 15:47.490
And l don't see any state seals
or shipping dates on any of these.

15:47.577 --> 15:51.028
Mr. Moran, you're not buying this
on the black market, are you?

15:51.205 --> 15:55.285
l bought this stuff all legal,
and you can bank that at Barclays.

15:55.918 --> 15:58.290
Then where are the state seals?

16:00.381 --> 16:02.789
We're gonna have to
confiscate this as contraband.

16:02.884 --> 16:05.671
FACE: Colonel Lexington,
could you give me a hand, please?

16:05.803 --> 16:07.879
-Delighted.
-No, look....

16:08.723 --> 16:10.514
[Moran stuttering]

16:30.912 --> 16:32.157
SCHECKTER: Ever see him before?

16:32.246 --> 16:34.998
Probably came down
from the high country for supplies.

16:42.215 --> 16:45.465
HANNlBAL: Can you show me on the map
a way through Solomon's Pass?

16:45.551 --> 16:49.003
TOBY: Our route would be through this
passage here. Solomon's Pass.

16:49.096 --> 16:51.884
The roads may be a bit rough,
but monsoon season is over...

16:51.974 --> 16:54.512
so there's not much of a danger of slides.

16:54.602 --> 16:58.682
TOBY: lf we start at first light and
we're lucky, we should make it by nightfall.

16:58.773 --> 17:03.102
You're gonna need more than luck, darling.
You've been warned about this, Miss Griffin.

17:03.194 --> 17:04.818
You know this piece of cheese?

17:04.904 --> 17:08.439
Take a little healthy advice, mister.
Don't work for that lady.

17:08.532 --> 17:12.198
lt's rough country out there, you might get
bitten in the middle of the night.

17:12.286 --> 17:13.483
Great.

17:13.746 --> 17:16.580
Since l gave up golf,
my life has been real boring.

17:16.665 --> 17:18.789
TOBY: The mine was my father's, Scheckter.

17:18.876 --> 17:22.790
The claim was properly filed in Salisbury.
And l'm going to work it.

17:23.089 --> 17:24.749
Otherwise, he died for nothing.

17:24.839 --> 17:26.464
You try to work that mine...

17:26.550 --> 17:29.551
and you might have
the same kind of accident that killed him.

17:29.637 --> 17:32.045
They say bad luck runs in families.

17:32.139 --> 17:35.840
HANNlBAL: l've heard it's the same
with stupidity. Or was it ugliness?

17:37.562 --> 17:40.432
[Fast-paced instrumental music]

18:09.260 --> 18:10.802
Thanks, B.A.

18:23.900 --> 18:25.275
Nice, B.A.

18:31.699 --> 18:34.107
You're gonna die for this, mister.

18:34.202 --> 18:35.862
Come on, ladies.

18:36.954 --> 18:38.496
Come on, B.A.

18:41.334 --> 18:43.291
[Sinister instrumental music]

18:52.053 --> 18:53.381
[Phone ringing]

18:57.433 --> 18:58.512
Yes.

18:58.601 --> 19:00.060
SCHECKTER: Scheckter.
I'm at the Come Lucky.

19:00.603 --> 19:01.931
Scheckter, yes?

19:02.021 --> 19:04.856
SCHECKTER: I'm sorry, Mr. FIetcher,
we messed up.

19:05.942 --> 19:08.065
You're not paid to mess up!

19:08.611 --> 19:11.565
You kill them if you have to!
No one opens that mine but me!

19:11.697 --> 19:13.073
You understand?

19:16.452 --> 19:18.990
[Upbeat instrumental music]

19:25.211 --> 19:26.919
[Murdock yelling]

19:29.924 --> 19:33.209
l'm warning you, Murdock.
l got enough trouble with these roads...

19:33.302 --> 19:35.259
without you making all that stupid noise.

19:35.346 --> 19:38.929
Take it easy, B.A. How's this thing doing?

19:39.308 --> 19:41.182
This thing is running terrible.

19:41.310 --> 19:43.552
Seems like it's come from
one of Face's scams.

19:43.646 --> 19:46.600
Let's not get personal
when we have company.

19:48.442 --> 19:50.815
-How much further is it?
-About 20 miles.

19:50.903 --> 19:54.438
That is if Scheckter and his men
don't try to kill us first.

19:54.532 --> 19:56.904
They'll try. The question is where.

20:02.999 --> 20:06.617
You take Jaspers and Baker over
to Solomon's Pass just west of the ravine.

20:06.711 --> 20:07.790
Ambush them.

20:07.879 --> 20:10.630
No problem.
Just like we do with old man Griffin.

20:10.715 --> 20:14.712
SCHECKTER: We'll go back to the mine,
clean out the rest of those workers.

20:15.636 --> 20:19.219
We'll see you back at Fletcher's.
Turn them inside out.

20:27.440 --> 20:30.856
Keep driving like that,
and you'll get us there in a big ball of fire.

20:30.943 --> 20:32.319
Don't tell me how to drive, man.

20:32.403 --> 20:35.606
ls this what l get for $210,000?

20:35.740 --> 20:38.610
Come on, this is the way it's done
in all the Tarzan movies!

20:38.701 --> 20:39.946
-That's right.
-Sure.

20:40.036 --> 20:44.662
First, the pretty lady hires a safari to help
her find the legendary elephant graveyard.

20:44.749 --> 20:47.833
Then one of the jungle party goes mad
from drinking swamp water.

20:47.919 --> 20:50.077
Ten days later, they're hopelessly lost!

20:50.171 --> 20:53.622
The porters abandon them as
they've crossed into the land of bad magic.

20:53.716 --> 20:54.747
Things are bad.

20:54.842 --> 20:57.629
Just as they are about to fall prey
to the savage natives--

20:57.720 --> 21:01.219
Some dude in a loincloth and a $40 haircut
swings in and saves the day.

21:01.307 --> 21:02.801
[Murdock whoops]

21:03.059 --> 21:06.013
-How's it going back there, Face?
-Not good, Colonel.

21:06.103 --> 21:09.057
Gets real unstable when it's wet,
and it's sweating pretty good.

21:09.190 --> 21:13.104
l'm an expert on unstable.
This stuff is not unstable!

21:13.319 --> 21:16.522
This stuff won't even go off
without a blasting cap.

21:16.739 --> 21:18.150
Fraidy cats--

21:18.324 --> 21:19.949
AMY: Murdock!

21:20.243 --> 21:21.820
Brilliant, Murdock.

21:34.173 --> 21:36.047
We give this stuff one more good bounce...

21:36.133 --> 21:38.375
and Murdock'll be telling his jokes
to St. Peter.

21:38.469 --> 21:39.750
He's already heard them.

21:39.887 --> 21:41.844
[Singing in bad Latin]

21:51.899 --> 21:53.559
Hang tight, B.A.

21:56.112 --> 21:58.817
[Fast-paced instrumental music]

22:16.591 --> 22:20.754
Go back up to the jeep and call Scheckter.
Tell him we've got these guys pinned down.

22:20.845 --> 22:22.469
JASPERS: Right.
VANATTA: Go!

22:24.390 --> 22:27.225
HANNlBAL: Face, take the left.
Murdock, you take the right.

22:27.310 --> 22:29.717
Get up the hill and flank them.
We'll keep them busy.

22:29.812 --> 22:32.517
B.A., cover us.
l'll get the women away from the dynamite.

22:32.607 --> 22:34.730
Ready, go!

22:34.817 --> 22:37.652
[Fast-paced instrumental music continues]

23:16.150 --> 23:19.899
B.A.: My gun is jammed, Hannibal.
HANNlBAL: Here, take this.

23:21.072 --> 23:23.563
Stand by to heat it up. l'm going.

23:23.658 --> 23:25.152
Hannibal, where are you going?

23:25.243 --> 23:27.864
-The front door. Where else?
-Stupid question.

23:31.290 --> 23:34.457
MURDOCK: lt's Bogey the Bear time.
Freeze it!

23:40.049 --> 23:42.338
Bogey the Bear said, ''Freeze it!''

24:06.242 --> 24:09.326
Make a move
and l'll turn you into fruit salad.

24:11.080 --> 24:12.954
HANNlBAL: On your feet, pal.

24:13.875 --> 24:17.872
You guys throw a heck of a party.
Looks like l got the door prize.

24:20.339 --> 24:21.834
[Murdock exclaims]

24:24.760 --> 24:27.002
-You all right, Murdock?
-Yes.

24:27.096 --> 24:30.346
l don' t think Bogey
is gonna make it, Lieutenant.

24:31.184 --> 24:33.057
FACE: Too bad.
B.A.: Hannibal!

24:33.644 --> 24:36.645
We lost this wheel and half the axle.

24:38.065 --> 24:40.901
We ain't going nowhere, unless we walk.

24:40.985 --> 24:44.271
-How far is it to the mine, Miss Griffin?
-Too far.

24:44.697 --> 24:46.606
[Tense instrumental music]

24:52.997 --> 24:55.488
HANNlBAL: An abandoned truck?
You're putting me on.

24:55.583 --> 24:59.663
FACE: Right up over the ridge. l almost fell
over it while l was chasing those guys.

24:59.754 --> 25:02.245
HANNlBAL: Face, you're turning luck
into an art form.

25:02.340 --> 25:06.669
Art form's a bit much. l prefer to think of it
as talent for the remarkable.

25:06.886 --> 25:09.293
This truck, was it an old blue pickup?

25:09.430 --> 25:13.262
Yeah. Rusted-out paint job,
some kind of artwork on the door.

25:13.434 --> 25:16.554
FACE: Bird, gargoyle, something like that.
TOBY: A griffin.

25:16.646 --> 25:19.979
He painted that stupid thing
on the door by himself.

25:20.900 --> 25:22.976
Thought it protected him.

25:23.402 --> 25:26.818
Man, the parts we need
could still be on her daddy's truck.

25:26.906 --> 25:31.484
-l can get them and fix this thing.
-lt's a great idea, B.A. Give it a try.

25:31.619 --> 25:33.161
HANNlBAL: Come on, Face.

25:36.415 --> 25:38.040
What are you guys gonna do with us?

25:38.167 --> 25:41.453
We thought maybe we'd tie you to a tree
and leave you for the lions.

25:41.546 --> 25:43.455
They Iike a IittIe snack at night.

25:43.631 --> 25:45.956
They get the munchies, right after Carson.

25:46.050 --> 25:47.877
Could try the old lndian trick.

25:47.969 --> 25:51.468
-Stake them out over an anthill?
-l've always liked it.

25:51.556 --> 25:54.889
l don't know. l'm not sure
how l'd get the ants to go for these two.

25:54.976 --> 25:57.977
lt's easy. Just stick an ice-cream cone
right in their pocket.

25:58.062 --> 25:59.260
You guys are crazy.

25:59.355 --> 26:02.938
He is crazy. We are just bad-tempered.
Okay, start walking.

26:03.734 --> 26:06.356
VANATTA: What, you're letting us go?
HANNlBAL: For now.

26:06.988 --> 26:11.116
-We'll never make it back on foot.
-Try it on your hands and knees. Move it.

26:13.494 --> 26:15.487
Give Fletcher my regards.

26:16.664 --> 26:17.944
Move it!

26:23.421 --> 26:25.544
[Soft sentimental instrumental music]

26:29.093 --> 26:32.213
The damage is on the top.
We can still get what we need.

26:33.347 --> 26:35.589
He never had a chance, did he?

26:36.934 --> 26:38.097
No.

26:40.771 --> 26:42.266
You okay, Toby?

26:44.233 --> 26:47.151
You can get the parts.
ls that what you said?

26:50.114 --> 26:52.783
You know,
once three men beat up my father.

26:52.867 --> 26:55.654
They hurt him real bad. He almost died.

26:56.037 --> 27:00.284
It ain't the same, I reaIise that.
I know you're so mad you want to bust.

27:00.374 --> 27:04.039
But don't worry. Them guys
that got your father, they're gonna pay.

27:04.253 --> 27:06.210
You got my word on that.

27:13.137 --> 27:14.964
[Rhythmic instrumental music]

27:26.484 --> 27:28.192
Hurry up, you fool!

28:10.069 --> 28:11.729
You ready, B.A.?

28:12.780 --> 28:15.318
lt won't win no lndy 500,
but it'll get us there.

28:15.408 --> 28:17.281
HANNlBAL: Let's go, Miss Griffin.

28:21.873 --> 28:25.704
You know, B.A., with a pair of pliers
and a little time...

28:26.836 --> 28:28.828
you could fix anything but dinner.

28:29.005 --> 28:31.543
[Rhythmic instrumental music resumes]

29:05.374 --> 29:07.118
You know, Toby...

29:07.710 --> 29:11.660
we don't have to maintain
this client-employee relationship forever.

29:11.756 --> 29:16.382
l mean, after you work the mine for a couple
of months, get it going good, we could...

29:16.469 --> 29:18.011
meet in Hawaii.

29:18.346 --> 29:21.762
l have access to a real nice condo
on the Big lsland.

29:21.933 --> 29:24.850
We could study volcanic eruptions together.

29:28.397 --> 29:32.609
On the other hand, we could just have
a quick drink in Johannesburg.

29:36.948 --> 29:38.987
[Elephants trumpeting]

29:39.200 --> 29:43.032
Guys, without the risk of sounding
melodramatic, goodbye forever!

30:07.520 --> 30:08.979
Pull up here.

30:10.898 --> 30:13.685
The air's beginning to feel a little richer.

30:13.776 --> 30:15.852
Like those diamonds know we're coming.

30:15.945 --> 30:19.195
They're very intelligent, you know.
They have many facets.

30:19.282 --> 30:21.986
When you get to know them,
most of them are absolute gems.

30:22.076 --> 30:24.911
Why do you want to stop here?
lt's only another few minutes.

30:24.996 --> 30:26.620
That stretch of road up there.

30:26.706 --> 30:30.324
Now, that isn't where l'd like to see
the A-Team memorial plaque erected.

30:30.418 --> 30:33.751
That's Solomon's Pass.
My father's mine's not far beyond.

30:33.838 --> 30:37.456
The road winds through the pass
and ends up there, at the top of the cliff.

30:37.550 --> 30:40.504
We have to go all the way there
in order to get back up here?

30:40.595 --> 30:41.793
lt's the only way.

30:41.929 --> 30:45.096
Didn't anybody consider
putting in an escalator? Come on.

30:45.183 --> 30:48.433
-Do l have to think of everything?
-Believe me, it's the only way.

30:48.519 --> 30:50.761
l've been here hundreds of times
with my father.

30:50.855 --> 30:52.349
l'm sure you have.

30:52.440 --> 30:54.563
When l jump into
that sleazy Fletcher's mind...

30:54.692 --> 30:57.978
l'd find the first place
l'd put an ambush is in Solomon's Pass.

30:58.237 --> 31:00.989
Wait. We're talking
about vertical here, Hannibal.

31:01.073 --> 31:02.616
Very.

31:02.700 --> 31:04.242
Sergeant...

31:04.327 --> 31:06.652
how do you feel
about a little mountain climbing?

31:06.746 --> 31:09.830
Ain't no big thing. All it is,
is a whole lot of chin-ups.

31:09.916 --> 31:12.916
-Just don't put me in no flying machine.
-Wouldn't think of it.

31:13.002 --> 31:16.086
l want you to get up there
as soon as you can and drop me a rope.

31:16.172 --> 31:18.793
l want to pack that dynamite up the cliff.

31:18.883 --> 31:21.800
That's suicide.
This stuff's sweating like it's got a fever.

31:21.886 --> 31:25.136
lf we don't get the dynamite to the mine,
there's no sense going.

31:25.223 --> 31:28.307
HANNlBAL: Face, give B.A. that rope.
FACE: Right.

31:28.392 --> 31:30.432
You're crazier than Murdock.

31:30.520 --> 31:33.189
l'd pull it up with a block and tackle,
but we can't.

31:33.272 --> 31:36.357
One bad bounce and the lights go out.
lt's going up on my back.

31:36.442 --> 31:37.521
B.A.: Don't touch that.

31:37.610 --> 31:40.564
You get on the jazz
with a pack of dynamite on your back...

31:40.655 --> 31:42.980
it'll blow a hole big enough
to bury an elephant.

31:43.074 --> 31:45.280
l'll get the dynamite. You stay away from it.

31:45.368 --> 31:48.784
Now somebody got to help me with this.
l can't do it by myself.

31:48.871 --> 31:51.196
All right, l'll take the rope up.

31:54.335 --> 31:57.040
HANNlBAL: And you need a volunteer, right?
B.A.: Right.

31:57.463 --> 31:58.578
Right.

31:58.673 --> 32:02.338
Don't you smile at me like that.
That's not even a real smile.

32:02.635 --> 32:05.589
Just a bunch of teeth playing with my mind!

32:27.076 --> 32:29.863
VANATTA: Why didn't you come back for us?
We could have died!

32:29.954 --> 32:32.445
Enough! Where are they now?

32:32.540 --> 32:35.541
JASPER: They fixed the truck.
Passed us when we were walking back.

32:35.626 --> 32:38.200
They are going northeast.
Probably heading for the mine.

32:38.379 --> 32:40.917
Before they get there,
we'll stop them in the pass.

32:41.132 --> 32:44.049
They've had a very long drive
in a jerry-rigged truck...

32:44.135 --> 32:46.922
and we have the helicopter.
Care to make any wagers?

32:47.013 --> 32:49.586
lt may not be that easy.
They get through that pass...

32:49.682 --> 32:51.722
they can pick up reinforcements at the mine.

32:51.809 --> 32:54.514
We'll fly there first,
and scatter those workers for good.

32:54.604 --> 32:57.605
Tell Scheckter we'll back them up
at the mine.

33:06.032 --> 33:07.823
HANNlBAL: You two all right?
AMY: Yeah.

33:07.909 --> 33:10.993
AMY: Murdock, are you okay?
l thought l heard some buzzing.

33:11.078 --> 33:13.237
What else do you expect from the...

33:13.915 --> 33:15.325
human fly?

33:15.416 --> 33:18.750
The climber of walls, source of annoyance...

33:19.128 --> 33:22.331
ruiner of picnics, sticky of foot!

33:22.840 --> 33:25.047
HANNlBAL: B.A., Face, okay.

33:25.468 --> 33:27.757
[Suspenseful instrumental music]

33:46.948 --> 33:48.905
l hope the packs hold.

33:48.991 --> 33:51.399
-What if--
-lf they don't hold...

33:51.869 --> 33:54.491
that's about it. Just about where we're at.

34:18.437 --> 34:20.014
Look out, Face!

34:31.409 --> 34:33.734
FACE: B.A., your pack's coming open!

34:42.753 --> 34:43.868
They're all right.

34:48.592 --> 34:52.210
That blast came from the cliff area.
Give me the glasses.

34:52.679 --> 34:54.637
[Tense instrumental music]

34:59.979 --> 35:01.888
Try and raise Fletcher.

35:13.534 --> 35:16.654
All right, nail down exactly where they are
and zero me in.

35:16.787 --> 35:19.076
Will do. We're opening up on them now.

35:32.053 --> 35:35.303
HANNlBAL: We'll have to run for the mines,
Toby, can you get us there?

35:35.389 --> 35:37.678
All right. Face, stick with her.
You got the point?

35:37.767 --> 35:41.930
Murdock and l'll give coverage fire.
B.A., l'll bring up the rear.

35:44.941 --> 35:46.732
HANNlBAL: You ready?
FACE: Ready.

35:47.068 --> 35:48.562
Murdock, go!

35:55.243 --> 35:57.816
They're headed straight for the main shaft
of the mine.

35:57.912 --> 35:59.786
SCHECKTER: Pick them up,
we'II foIIow them.

35:59.872 --> 36:01.153
Got you.

36:01.249 --> 36:03.574
[Fast-paced instrumental music]

36:40.246 --> 36:43.946
-What are we going to do now?
-The thing is, what are they gonna do?

36:44.041 --> 36:46.746
Probably blow the mine.
We end up under a pile of rocks...

36:46.836 --> 36:48.295
and they go home. Nice and neat.

36:48.379 --> 36:50.621
HANNlBAL: ls there another exit out of here?
TOBY: No.

36:50.798 --> 36:53.467
We sure could use that air shaft
you wanted, right now.

36:53.634 --> 36:56.837
Fletcher wouldn't blow this mine.
He wants to work it.

36:57.096 --> 37:00.180
That's why he hired Alan Scheckter
to kill my father.

37:00.266 --> 37:04.050
-Yeah, and now us.
-Hannibal, can we go home now?

37:04.645 --> 37:06.519
[Tense instrumental music]

37:35.092 --> 37:38.093
Sorry, Mr. Fletcher.
Griffin's kid hired some real muscle.

37:38.179 --> 37:39.459
These guys are good.

37:39.597 --> 37:42.930
SCHECKTER: They probably have
enough ammo to hold us off all night.

37:45.436 --> 37:47.725
We'll attack them in the morning.

37:47.813 --> 37:50.435
Scheckter, you take Landers
and get some tear gas.

37:50.525 --> 37:53.016
We'll stand guard here until you do.

37:53.611 --> 37:56.149
We'll flush them out in the morning.

38:07.959 --> 38:10.497
Where're all the workers
that were supposed to be here?

38:10.586 --> 38:12.460
This lantern was lit when we ran in here.

38:12.547 --> 38:15.880
Fletcher probably ran them off.
Just like he tried to run off my dad.

38:15.967 --> 38:18.292
-Terrific.
-We better get started.

38:18.678 --> 38:23.007
lf this thing goes by the numbers, those
goons will be storming this place at sunrise.

38:26.102 --> 38:28.771
Hannibal, we got
a regular hardware store here.

38:28.855 --> 38:31.891
My dad was moving equipment in here
for months.

38:32.942 --> 38:34.222
Hey B.A.

38:34.318 --> 38:37.485
Remember that two-man patrol
we did in Cambodia?

38:38.531 --> 38:39.776
Yeah.

38:39.866 --> 38:42.950
l think l can rig something up. lt'll be nice.

38:43.035 --> 38:45.906
HANNlBAL: Face, give us
that acetylene torch.

38:45.997 --> 38:48.155
[Adventurous instrumental music]

40:31.519 --> 40:35.386
-You men in there, can you hear me?
-Can't hear a word.

40:35.481 --> 40:38.352
Come on out in one minute
or we'll blow the mine.

40:38.442 --> 40:42.226
You're bluffing.
You want this hole in the dirt left open.

40:42.321 --> 40:46.449
-You won't blow it. Try again.
-You can't stay in there forever.

40:46.534 --> 40:49.321
There's only one way out,
and it's target practice for us.

40:49.412 --> 40:50.823
Give it up or you'll starve.

40:50.913 --> 40:54.745
Don't worry about us.
We'll send out to the corner deli.

41:01.257 --> 41:02.420
You guys ready?

41:02.508 --> 41:05.960
You bet l am. l'm gonna pay those guys
back for what they did to Bogey.

41:06.053 --> 41:07.880
-The fool's crazy!
-Now, Murdock...

41:07.972 --> 41:10.048
when we drop the hammer,
head for the chopper.

41:10.141 --> 41:13.261
l've got a hunch when things get hot,
Fletcher's gonna split.

41:14.228 --> 41:16.304
HANNlBAL: You ready, B.A.?
B.A.: Ready.

41:16.397 --> 41:17.725
FACE: Tear gas!

41:55.228 --> 41:57.553
[Fast-paced instrumental music]

42:29.095 --> 42:32.345
Keep that gun on them. These guys
will admit Fletcher hired them.

42:32.431 --> 42:33.760
HANNlBAL: We'll indict him.

42:33.850 --> 42:36.601
-lf he doesn't get away first.
-He won't.

43:37.371 --> 43:39.031
FLETCHER: Help!

43:40.124 --> 43:41.998
FLETCHER: Are you crazy?

43:48.841 --> 43:52.340
[Upbeat instrumental music]

44:07.944 --> 44:10.980
lt's the ball game, Coach.
Got the whole team.

44:17.703 --> 44:19.495
How we getting home?

44:22.291 --> 44:25.043
Somebody better give me an answer quick,
before l get mad.

44:25.127 --> 44:29.291
l told you, that's not my end of the rope.
l run my department, Hannibal runs his.

44:29.382 --> 44:31.291
-Ask him.
-How'd it go?

44:31.384 --> 44:34.753
Scheckter and his grizzle are gonna testify
that Fletcher hired them.

44:34.846 --> 44:36.553
They'll put him away for a long time.

44:36.639 --> 44:40.222
Maybe now some of the people in this town
won't be afraid to work for me.

44:40.309 --> 44:42.551
Hannibal, how are we gonna get home?

44:42.645 --> 44:46.643
That's Murdock's end of the operation.
l'm just a single man...

44:46.732 --> 44:49.306
working against insurmountable odds.

44:50.570 --> 44:52.977
l said, ''How?''
Tell me or l'll break your head!

44:53.072 --> 44:55.029
MURDOCK: lt's already broken.

44:58.327 --> 44:59.572
[Laughing] Sucker.

45:01.789 --> 45:03.414
Tried to get me.

45:09.463 --> 45:10.792
Excuse us.

45:11.632 --> 45:13.210
HANNlBAL: Murdock, give us a hand.

45:13.301 --> 45:16.670
Thanks. Really.
You guys might be a little unique...

45:17.096 --> 45:18.555
but you're great.

45:19.307 --> 45:20.552
Just one more thing.

45:20.641 --> 45:22.385
-What's that?
-The diamond.

45:22.476 --> 45:25.892
You don't get your collateral back
until we get our 10%% of the mine.

45:30.276 --> 45:32.150
Business is business.

45:41.245 --> 45:43.119
[Theme music]

